<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>If there is an element having class with hyphen in name, eg.</p>

<p>&lt;</p>

<p>div class="class-one"&gt; and one queries for such element using second class name:</p>

<p>$dom-&gt;query('.class-one');</p>

<p>the element is not matched (query returns empty result), but only if the element is any level child of an element having two classes.</p>

<p>For instance, the above query will work in the the following case:</p>

<div class="class1"><div class="class-one"></div></div>

<p>but not in the one below:</p>

<div class="class1 class2"><div class="class-one"></div></div>

<p>Already tagged 1.9.7 release is also affected.</p>

    </div>
